<html
	xmlns:c = "http://www.classesarecode.net/pistol/core"
	xmlns:e = "http://www.classesarecode.net/pistol/entity"
	xmlns:i18n = "http://www.classesarecode.net/pistol/i18n"
	xmlns:md = "http://www.classesarecode.net/pistol/md"
	xmlns:string = "http://www.classesarecode.net/pistol/string"
	xmlns:html = "http://www.classesarecode.net/pistol/html">
	<head>
		<title>Pistol Documentation - string:size</title>
	</head>
	<body>
		<h1>string:size</h1>
		<p>This pad with spaces or chop a string to it is a specific length.</p>
		<p><e:lt/>string:size length="10"<e:gt/>Shorten to 10 characters<e:lt/>/string:size<e:gt/> will result in</p>
		<p><string:size length="10">Shorten to 10 characters</string:size></p>
		<p><e:lt/>string:size length="40"<e:gt/>Lengthen to 40 characters<e:lt/>/string:size<e:gt/> will result in</p>
		<p><string:size length="40">Lengthen to 40 characters</string:size></p>
		<p>Note: view the source to see the full effect</p>
	</body>	
</html>